Error: Error: "Allocating More RAM To Minecraft Makes The Server Crash"

Solution: 1. Log in to the Pterodactyl panel and select the Minecraft server that is experiencing the issue.

2. Click on the "Console" section and stop the server if it is currently running. 

3. Click on the "File Manager" section, then navigate to the "server.properties" file and click on it to open.

